obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (40854)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 31st January, 2018, vide notification No. S.O. 149(E), dated 11th January, 2018, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40854&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Institutes of Management`
  line `Act, 2017.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (40855)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration of certain institutions as institutions of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40855&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Whereas the objects of the`
  line `Institutes mentioned in the Schedule are such as to make them institutions of national importance, it is`
  line `hereby declared that each such Institute is an institution of national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (40856)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2019, s. 3 and Sch. II, for '"Director", means' (w.e.f. 8-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40856&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Academic Council" means the Academic Council referred to in section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board", in relation to any Institute, means the Board of Governors referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Board of Governors of the Institutes appointed`
  line `under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) "Coordination Forum" means the Coordination Forum established under section 29;`
  line
  line `(e) "corresponding Institute", in relation to an Institute mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule,`
  line `means an Institute as specified against the said Institute in column (5);`
  line
  line `(f) ^1["Director" means] the Director of the Institute appointed under sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(g) "existing Institute" means any Institute mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(h) "Institute" means any Institute mentioned in column (5) of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(i) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression "notify"`
  line `with its cognate meanings and grammatical variation shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(j) "Ordinances" means Ordinances made by the Academic Council under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "regulations" means regulations made by the Board;`
  line
  line `(m) "Schedule" means the Schedule annexed to this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "society" means any of the societies registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860`
  line `(21 of 1860) or the Mysore Societies' Registration Act, 1960 (17 of 1960) or the Madhya Pradesh`
  line `Societies Registration Act, 1973 (44 of 1973) or the Tamil Nadu Societies Registration Act, 1975`
  line `(27 of 1975) or the Jammu and Kashmir Societies Registration Act, 1998 (VI of 1998) mentioned in`
  line `column (3) of the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (40857)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Incorporation of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40857&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every Institute shall be a body corporate by the same name as`
  line `mentioned in column (5) of the Schedule.]`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) On and from the date of commencement of the Indian Institutes of Management (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 2023, the National Institute of Industrial Engineering, Mumbai, shall be called the "Indian Institute`
  line `of Management, Mumbai" and all the provisions of this Act shall apply to the said Institute.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1B) On and from the date of commencement of the Indian Institutes of Management (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 2025, all the provisions of this Act shall apply to the Indian Institute of Management, Guwahati.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every Institute referred to in column (5) of the Schedule shall have perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 31 of 2025, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 01-09-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-08-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 31 of 2025, s. 2 (w.e.f. 01-09-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (40858)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Effect of incorporation of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40858&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the commencement of this Act,---`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to an existing Institute in any contract or other instrument shall be deemed as a`
  line `reference to the corresponding Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) all properties, movable and immovable, of or belonging to every existing Institute shall vest in`
  line `the corresponding Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) all rights and debts and other liabilities of every existing Institute shall be transferred to, and be`
  line `the rights and liabilities of, the corresponding Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) ^1[every person, other than a Director employed by every existing Institute] immediately before such commencement`
  line `shall hold his office or service in the corresponding Institute, with the same tenure, at the same`
  line `remuneration and upon the same terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to`
  line `pension, leave, gratuity, provident fund and other matters as he would have held had this Act not been`
  line `enacted and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment is terminated or until such tenure,`
  line `remuneration and terms and conditions are duly altered by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the alteration so made is not acceptable to such employee, his employment may be`
  line `terminated by the Institute in accordance with the terms of the contract with the employee, or, if no provision`
  line `is made therein in this behalf, on payment, to him by the Institute, of a compensation equivalent to three`
  line `months' remuneration in case of permanent employee and one months' remuneration in the case of other`
  line `employee:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any reference, by whatever form of words, to the Director, and other officers of`
  line `an existing Institute under any law for the time being in force, or in any instrument or other document,`
  line `shall be construed as a reference to the Director, and other officers of the corresponding Institutes;`
  line
  line `^2[Provided also that the provisions of the first proviso shall also be applicable to the Directors of the`
  line Institutes;]
  line
  line `(e) every person pursuing, before commencement of this Act, any academic or research course in`
  line `every existing Institute, shall be deemed to have migrated and registered with the corresponding`
  line `Institute, on such commencement at the same level of course in the Institute from which such person`
  line migrated;
  line
  line `(f) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or against an`
  line `existing Institute, immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall be continued or instituted by`
  line `or against the corresponding Institute.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that in relation to the Indian`
  line `Institute of Management, Mumbai, the reference to the following expressions in sections 4 and 5---`
  line
  line `(i) "On and from the commencement of this Act";`
  line
  line `(ii) "before such commencement";`
  line
  line `(iii) "before commencement of this Act"; and`
  line
  line `(iv) "before the commencement of this Act",`
  line
  line `shall be construed as the reference to the date on which the provisions of the Indian Institutes of`
  line `Management (Amendment) Act, 2023 comes into force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub. by Act 23 of 2023, s. 3, for "every person employed by every existing Institute" (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 3, ibid., (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (40859)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Objects of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40859&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Each Institute shall have the following objects, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to educate and support leaders who can contribute as professional managers, entrepreneurs, and`
  line `stewards of existing and emerging enterprises in the private, public, and social sectors;`
  line
  line `(b) to carry out research, publication, consultancy and advisory work to advance new knowledge`
  line `and innovation and to provide global leadership in management theory and practice:`
  line
  line `Provided that research so conducted shall also be directed towards such areas of study which shall`
  line `enhance inclusive, equitable and sustainable national development goals as enshrined in the objects of the`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(c) to provide management education of high quality and to promote allied areas of knowledge as`
  line `well as interdisciplinary studies;`
  line
  line `(d) to sensitise management education to the vision of inclusive, equitable and sustainable national`
  line `development goals in order to contribute holistically to Society;`
  line
  line `(e) to support and develop programmes promoting social and gender equity;`
  line
  line `(f) to develop educational programmes and faculties that advance the cause of education, teaching`
  line `and learning, across disciplines;`
  line
  line `(g) to set-up centres for management studies and allied areas;`
  line
  line `(h) to support and collaborate with management institutions and other educational institutions in`
  line India;
  line
  line `(i) to co-operate and collaborate with educational or management institutions in other countries to`
  line `extend the interests of management education and research.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (40860)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Powers and functions of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40860&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, every Institute shall`
  line `exercise the following powers and perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to carry out the administration and management of the Institutes;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide by regulations for the admission of candidates to the various courses of study in`
  line `conformity with the laws for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(c) to specify and conduct courses of study, training and research in management and allied`
  line `subjects and document, and disseminate knowledge thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) to evolve innovative management education pedagogy aligned to dynamic global management`
  line practices;
  line
  line `(e) to conduct examinations and to establish processes for evaluation and performance assessment`
  line `through a fair and transparent system;`
  line
  line `(f) to grant degrees, diplomas and other academic distinctions or titles and to institute and award`
  line `fellowships, scholarships, prizes and medals, honorary awards and other distinctions;`
  line
  line `(g) to lower the cost of education and to enhance the reach of the education by use of information`
  line `and communication technology and other innovative methods;`
  line
  line `(h) to establish and maintain such infrastructure as may be necessary;`
  line
  line `(i) to determine, specify and receive payment of, fees and other charges as the Institute may deem`
  line `fit, from students and any other person, institution or body corporate for instruction and other services,`
  line `including training, consultancy and advisory services, provided by the Institute;`
  line
  line `(j) to acquire, hold and deal with the property belonging to or vested in the Institute, with the`
  line `approval of the Board, and in case of immovable property, under prior intimation to the Central`
  line `Government, for advancing the objects of the Institute subject to the condition that such property is`
  line `not obtained wholly or partly from the State Government or the Central Government funds:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the land for the Institute has been provided free of cost by a State Government`
  line `or the Central Government such land may be disposed of only with the prior approval of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(k) to create academic, administrative, technical, ministerial and other posts under the Institute`
  line `other than the post of Director of the Institute and to make appointments thereto;`
  line
  line `(l) to appoint committees for the disposal of any business of the Institute or for tendering advice in`
  line `any matter pertaining to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(m) to receive grants, gifts and contributions and to have custody of the funds including internally`
  line `generated funds of the Institute to meet the expenses, including capital expenditure of the Institute`
  line `including expenses incurred in the exercise of its powers and discharge of its functions;`
  line
  line `(n) to create partnership, affiliation and other classes of professional or honorary or technical`
  line `membership or office as the Institute may consider necessary;`
  line
  line `(o) to perform such other functions as may be necessary for carrying out the objects of the`
  line Institutes;
  line
  line `(p) to do all such things and activities, incidental to the attainment of all or any of the objects`
  line `of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (40861)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Institutes to be open to all irrespective of sex, race, creed, caste or class.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40861&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute`
  line `shall be open to all persons irrespective of sex, race, creed, caste or class, and no test or condition shall be`
  line `imposed as to religious belief or profession in admitting or appointing members, students, teachers or`
  line `workers or in any other connection whatsoever.`
  line
  line `(2) No bequest, donation or transfer of any property shall be accepted by any Institute which in the`
  line `opinion of the Board involves conditions or obligations opposed to the spirit and object of this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The admission to every academic course or programme of study in each Institute shall be based on`
  line `merit assessed through transparent and reasonable criteria disclosed through its prospectus, prior to the`
  line `commencement of the process of admission by such Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent the Institute from making special`
  line `provisions for the employment or admission of women, persons with disabilities or for persons belonging`
  line `to any socially and educationally backward classes of citizens and, in particular, for the Scheduled Castes`
  line `and the Scheduled Tribes:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every such Institute shall be a Central Educational Institution for the purposes of`
  line `the Central Educational Institutions (Reservation in Admission) Act, 2006 (5 of 2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (40862)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Institute to be not-for-profit legal entity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40862&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute shall be a not-for-profit legal entity`
  line `and no part of the surplus, if any, in revenue of such Institute, after meeting all expenditure in regard to`
  line `its operations under this Act, shall be invested for any purpose other than for the growth and development`
  line `of such Institute or for conducting research therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Institute shall strive to raise funds for self-sufficiency and sustainability.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (40863)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Board of Governors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40863&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Governors of each Institute shall be the principal`
  line `executive body of that Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of each Institute shall consist of the following members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, from amongst eminent persons distinguished in the field of industry or`
  line `education or science or technology or management or public administration or such other field,^1[to be`
  line `nominated by the Visitor];`
  line
  line `(b) one nominee of the Central Government having charge of the management education or his`
  line representative;
  line
  line `(c) one nominee of the respective State Government or representative of such nominees, within`
  line `whose territorial jurisdiction the Institute is located;`
  line
  line `(d) four eminent persons, of which at least one shall be a woman, distinguished in the field of`
  line `education, industry, commerce, social service or public administration, to be nominated by the Board,`
  line `having such experience and in such manner as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(e) two members from the faculty of respective Institutes to be nominated by the Chairperson, in`
  line `the manner to be laid down by the Board by regulations;`
  line
  line `(f) one person from the Scheduled Castes or Scheduled Tribes to be nominated by the Board from`
  line `amongst the members referred to in clauses (d), (e) and (g);`
  line
  line `(g) up to five persons to be co-opted by the Board from the alumni or the members of society of the`
  line `existing Institute who have distinguished themselves in the field of management:`
  line
  line `Provided that out of such five persons, not more than one member shall be from the Society;`
  line
  line `(h) three women members to be nominated by the Board from amongst the members referred to in`
  line `clauses (d), (e) and (g);`
  line
  line `(i) Director of the Institute, ex officio member.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may nominate a person to fill up any temporary vacancy, of a member referred to in clauses (d)`
  line `and (g) of sub-section (2), for a period which may extend to three months.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall designate an officer of the Institute to act as Secretary of the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson shall have the power to invite any number of experts, not being members of the`
  line `Board, to attend meetings of the Board, but such invitees shall not be entitled to vote at the meeting.`
  line
  line `^2[(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, if the Board is suspended or dissolved under`
  line `such conditions or procedure as may be prescribed, the Central Government shall constitute an interim`
  line `Board for a period of six months or till a regular Board is constituted as per the provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2023, s. 4, for "to be appointed by the Board" (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (76586)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title Visitor.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2023, s. 5, (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=76586&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Visitor.--- (1) The President of India shall be the Visitor of every Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Visitor may appoint one or more persons to review the work and progress of any Institute`
  line `and to hold inquiries into the affairs thereof and to report thereon in such manner as the Visitor may`
  line direct.
  line
  line `(3) The Board may also recommend to the Visitor, an inquiry as deemed proper against the`
  line `Institute which has not been functioning in accordance with the provisions and objectives of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon receipt of any such report referred to in sub-section (2), the Visitor may take such`
  line `action and issue such directions as he considers necessary in respect of any of the matters dealt with`
  line `in the report and the Institute shall be bound to comply with such directions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (40864)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Powers and functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40864&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board of every`
  line `Institute shall be responsible for the general superintendence, direction and control of the affairs of the`
  line `Institute and shall have the power to frame or amend or modify or rescind the regulations governing the`
  line `affairs of the Institute to achieve the objects of the Institute specified in section 6.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board shall have the following powers,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to take decisions on questions of policy relating to the administration and working of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(b) to examine and approve the annual budget estimates of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) to examine and approve the plan for development of the Institute and to identify sources of`
  line `finance for implementation of the plan;`
  line
  line `(d) to establish departments, faculties or schools of studies and initiate programmes or courses of`
  line `study at the Institute;`
  line
  line `(e) to set-up centres of management studies and allied areas within the country under intimation to`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) to grant degrees, diplomas and other academic distinctions or titles, and to institute and award`
  line `fellowships, scholarships, prizes and medals;`
  line
  line `(g) to confer honorary degrees in such manner as may be specified by the regulations;`
  line
  line `(h) to grant honorary awards and other distinctions;`
  line
  line `(i) to create academic, administrative, technical and other posts and to make appointments thereto:`
  line
  line `Provided that the cadre, the pay scales, allowances and term of employment of such posts shall be`
  line `such as may be determined by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(j) to determine, by regulations, the number and emoluments of such posts and to define the duties`
  line `and conditions of services of the academic, administrative, technical and other staff;`
  line
  line `(k) to set-up centres of management studies and allied areas outside India in accordance with`
  line `guidelines laid down by the Central Government from time to time and in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the laws for the time being in force in such foreign country;`
  line
  line `(l) to pay, variable pay to the Director of the Institute on the basis of performance objectives as`
  line `may be specified by the regulations;`
  line
  line `(m) to specify by regulations, the fees to be charged for courses of study and examinations in the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(n) to specify by regulations the manner of formation of department of teaching;`
  line
  line `(o) to specify by regulations the institution of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and`
  line prizes;
  line
  line `(p) to specify by regulations the qualifications, classification, terms of office and method of`
  line `appointment of the academic, administrative, technical and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(q) to specify by regulations the constitution of pension, insurance and provident funds for the`
  line `benefit of the academic, administrative, technical and other staff;`
  line
  line `(r) to specify by regulations, the establishment and maintenance of buildings;`
  line
  line `(s) to specify by regulations, the conditions of residence of students of the Institute and levying of fees`
  line `for residence in the halls and hostels and of other charges;`
  line
  line `(t) to specify by regulations, the manner of authentication of the orders and decisions of the Board;`
  line
  line `(u) to specify by regulations, the quorum for meetings of the Board, the Academic Council or any`
  line `Committee, and the procedures to be followed in the conduct of their business;`
  line
  line `(v) to specify by regulations, the financial accountability of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(w) to exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed`
  line `upon it by this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board may by regulations, delegate such powers and`
  line `functions of the Board to the Director as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall conduct an annual review of the performance of the Director, in the context of the`
  line `achievements of objects of the Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that such review shall include performance reviews of faculty members of the Institute on such`
  line `parameters, periodicity and terms of reference as may be determined by the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board shall, through an independent agency or group of experts, within a period of three years`
  line `from the date of incorporation of the Institute, and thereafter at least once every three years, evaluate and`
  line `review the performance of the Institutes, including its faculty, on the parameters of long term strategy and`
  line `rolling plans of the Institutes and such other parameters as the Board may decide and the report of such`
  line `review shall be placed in public domain.`
  line
  line `(6) The qualifications, experience and the manner of selection of the independent agency or group of`
  line `experts, referred to in sub-section (5), shall be such as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(7) The report of the evaluation and review under sub-section (5) shall be submitted by the Board to the`
  line `Central Government along with an action taken report thereon.`
  line
  line `(8) Where in the opinion of the Chairperson or the Director the situation is so emergent that an`
  line `immediate decision need to be taken in the interest of the Institute, the Chairperson, in consultation with`
  line `the Director may issue such orders as may be necessary, recording the grounds for his opinion:`
  line
  line `Provided that such orders shall be submitted for ratification by the Board in the next meeting.`
  line
  line `(9) The Board shall in the exercise of its power and discharge of its functions under this Act, be`
  line `accountable to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (40865)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Term of office of, vacancies among, and allowances payable to members of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2023, s. 6 (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40865&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save`
  line `as otherwise provided in this section, the term of office of the Chairperson or any other member of the`
  line `Board, other than an ex officio member, shall be four years from the date of his appointment or`
  line `nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that the term of office of a member nominated under clause (e) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 11 shall be two years from the date of his nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Chairperson, or any other member of the Board, other than an ex officio`
  line `member, may be appointed or nominated for a second term:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Chairperson or any other member of the Board, other than an ex officio member,`
  line `shall not be appointed or nominated for more than two consecutive terms.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, an outgoing Member shall, unless the`
  line `Board otherwise directs, continue in office until another person is appointed or nominated as a Member in`
  line `his place.]`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds the office by virtue of`
  line `which he is a member of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) A member of the Board, other than a nominee of the Central Government or the State Government,`
  line `who fails to attend three consecutive meetings of the Board without permission of the Chairperson, shall`
  line `cease to be a member of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) A casual vacancy of a member shall be filled up in accordance with the provisions of section 10.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of a member nominated to fill a casual vacancy shall continue for the remainder of`
  line `the term of the member in whose place he has been so nominated.`
  line
  line `(6) Members of the Board shall be entitled to such allowances, as may be specified in the regulations,`
  line `for attending meetings of the Board.`
  line
  line `(7) The Board shall meet at least once in every three months.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (40866)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Resignation of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40866&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson may, by notice in writing under his hand`
  line `addressed to the Board, resign from his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (40867)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Academic Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40867&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academic Council shall be the principal academic body of every`
  line `Institute, consisting of the following persons, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) Director of the Institute, who shall be the Chairperson of the Academic Council;`
  line
  line `(b) Deans in charge of academics, research, student affairs and such other functions of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) Chairs of Areas or Programmes, Heads or Coordinators of Faculties or Schools or Centres or`
  line `Departments, of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) all full time Faculty at the level of Professors and such number of other full time Faculty of the`
  line `Institute as may be determined by the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) such members, by invitation of the Board on the recommendation of the Director, who are`
  line `eminent in the fields of industry, finance, management, public administration and academics.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds the office by virtue of`
  line `which he is a member.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a member nominated under clause (d) of sub-section (1) shall be two years`
  line `from the date of his nomination.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (40868)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power and functions of Academic Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40868&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academic Council shall perform the`
  line `following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to specify the criteria and process for admission to courses or programmes of study offered by`
  line `the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) to specify the academic content of programmes and courses of study and undertake`
  line `modifications therein;`
  line
  line `(c) to specify the academic calendar, guidelines for conduct of examination and recommend grant of`
  line `degrees, diplomas and other academic distinctions or titles.`
  line
  line `(2) The Academic Council shall exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may`
  line `be conferred upon it, by this Act or the regulations or by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (40869)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title Director.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40869&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director shall be the Chief Executive Officer of the Institute and shall`
  line `provide leadership to the Institute and be responsible for implementation of the decisions of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall be ^1[appointed by the Board with prior approval of the Visitor, in such manner`
  line `and subject to such terms] and conditions of service as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `^2[(3) The Director shall be appointed out of the panel of names recommended by a search-cumselection committee to be constituted by the Board consisting of---`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson of the Board, who shall be the Chairperson of the search-cum-selection`
  line committee;
  line
  line `(b) one Member to be nominated by the Visitor; and`
  line
  line `(c) two Members chosen from amongst eminent administrators, industrialists, educationists,`
  line `scientists, technocrats and management specialists.`
  line
  line `(3A) The procedure to be adopted for selection of the Director shall be such as may be prescribed.].`
  line
  line `(4) The Director shall exercise the powers and perform the duties as may be assigned to him under this`
  line `Act or the regulations or as may be delegated to him by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may lay down the criteria to be followed by the Director while exercising`
  line `powers and performing his duties, which shall be evaluated by the Board annually, and if the Board is of`
  line `the opinion that such criteria has not been followed, then, the Board may, after giving an opportunity of`
  line `being heard to the Director, initiate action for removal of such Director under sub-section (7).`
  line
  line `(5) The Director shall, except on account of resignation or removal, hold office for a term of five`
  line `years, from the date on which he enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(6) The Director may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the Board, through the`
  line `Chairperson, resign his office at any time.`
  line
  line `(7) ^3[The Board, with prior approval of the Visitor, may remove from office the Director], who---`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Board, involves moral turpitude;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Director; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as a`
  line `Director; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position or so conducted himself as to render his continuance in office`
  line `prejudicial to the public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Director shall not be removed from office except by an order made by the Board,`
  line `after an enquiry instituted by it in which the Director has been informed of the charges against him and`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in respect of those charges.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the post of Director is likely to fall vacant on account of completion of tenure, the Board`
  line `shall initiate the process of appointment nine months prior to the occurrence of such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(9) Where the post of Director falls vacant on account of any reason, the Board may appoint the`
  line `senior-most faculty in the institution as the Director in charge till a regular Director is appointed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the senior-most faculty is not willing to hold the post of Director in charge, then the`
  line `next senior-most willing faculty may be appointed as Director in charge.`
  line
  line `^4[(10) The services of the Director may be terminated by the Visitor, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2023, s. 7, for "appointed by the Board, on such terms" (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7,ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7 ibid., for "The Board may remove from office the Director" (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 7,ibid. (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (40870)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40870&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `[Initiation of inquiry].--- Omitted by the Indian Institutes of Management (Amendment) Act, 2023`
  line `(23 of 2023), s. 8 (w.e.f. 11-08-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (40871)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Custodian of records, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40871&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Board may designate any officer or officers of the Institute as`
  line `the custodian of records, common seal, funds of the Institute and any other property of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (40872)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Role of members of Society.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40872&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The members of the societies referred to at serial numbers 2 and 3`
  line `under column (3) of the Schedule, may be engaged by the respective Boards of corresponding Institutes,`
  line `for advisory assistance to it, by passing a resolution in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (40873)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Committees and other authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40873&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, constitute such committees and other`
  line `authorities of the Institute and specify the duties and functions of each such committees and authorities by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(2) The Board may constitute such ad hoc committees as it may deem fit, for proper management of`
  line `affairs of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (40874)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40874&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling the Institutes to discharge their`
  line `functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to every Institute such sums of money in such manner as it may`
  line `think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (40875)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Fund of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40875&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute shall maintain a Fund to which shall be credited—`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys provided by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and other charges received by the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys received by the Institute by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions, bequests or`
  line transfers;
  line
  line `(d) all moneys received by the Institute from utilisation of intellectual property arising from`
  line `research conducted or rendering advisory or consultancy services by it; and`
  line
  line `(e) all moneys received by the Institute in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys credited to the Fund of every Institute shall be deposited in such banks or invested in`
  line `such manner as may be laid down by the Board by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Each Institute shall create a corpus fund for long term sustainability of the Institute, to which shall`
  line `be credited such per cent. of the net income of the Institute and donations made specifically towards such`
  line `corpus fund as the Central Government may in accordance with the provisions of the Income tax Act,`
  line `1961 (43 of 1961), notify:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may also create endowment funds for specific purposes to which donations`
  line `may be specifically made.`
  line
  line `(4) The fund of any Institute shall be applied in such manner and for such purposes as may be`
  line `specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (40876)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40876&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute shall maintain proper accounts including income and`
  line `expenditure statements, internal audit report and statement audited by internal auditor specifying`
  line `investments and other relevant records and prepare annual statement of accounts including the balance`
  line `sheet in such form and as per such accounting standard as may be specified by notification by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the statement of income and expenditure and the balance sheet of the Institute do not`
  line `comply with the accounting standards, the Institute shall disclose in its statement of income and`
  line `expenditure and balance sheet, the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the deviation from the accounting standards;`
  line
  line `(b) the reasons for such deviation; and`
  line
  line `(c) the financial effect, if any, arising out of such deviation.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of every Institute shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and`
  line `any expenditure incurred by audit team in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Institute to the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Institute shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the offices of the`
  line Institute.
  line
  line `(5) The accounts of every Institute as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded annually`
  line `to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament in accordance with such procedure as may be laid down by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (40877)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Books of account to be maintained by Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40877&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Every Institute shall keep proper updated`
  line `books of account with respect to—`
  line
  line `(a) all sums of money received and expended by it and the matters in respect of which receipt and`
  line `expenditure takes place;`
  line
  line `(b) the assets and liabilities of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) the properties, movable and immovable of the Institute.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, if books of account give a true and fair view of the`
  line `state of affairs of the Institute and its transactions, it shall be deemed as proper books of account with`
  line `respect to the matters specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (40878)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Appointment of auditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40878&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of every Institute shall, prior to the end of every`
  line `financial year, and without prejudice to the provisions contained in the Comptroller and Auditor-General's`
  line `(Duties, Powers and Conditions of Service) Act, 1971 (56 of 1971) or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force containing provisions for audit of accounts by the Institutes, appoint such auditors including the`
  line `internal auditor, on such remuneration as it thinks appropriate, to scrutinise the balance sheet and the`
  line `statement of income and expenditure of such Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall change the auditors after every four years.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of every Institute shall constitute an Audit Committee to provide an expert advice on`
  line `effectiveness of internal control system, risk management and audit report to the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditor appointed under sub-section (1) or any person employed by him shall not have any`
  line `direct or indirect interest, whether pecuniary or otherwise, in any matter concerning or related to the`
  line `administration or functions of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (40879)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Annual report of Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40879&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be attached to every statement of accounts laid`
  line `before the Board of each Institute under section 27, a report, by its Director, with respect to—`
  line
  line `(a) the state of affairs of such Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the amounts, if any, which it proposes to carry to any surplus reserves in its balance sheet;`
  line
  line `(c) the extent to which understatement or overstatement of any surplus of income over expenditure or`
  line `any shortfall of expenditure over income has been indicated in the auditor's report and the reasons for such`
  line `understatement or overstatement;`
  line
  line `(d) the productivity of research projects undertaken by the Institute measured in accordance with`
  line `such norms as may be specified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) appointments of the officers and faculty members of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(f) performance indicators and internal standards set by the Institute, including the nature of`
  line `innovations in teaching, research and application of knowledge.`
  line
  line `(2) The report of the Director shall also include a statement showing the names of the five officers including`
  line `faculty members and other employees of the Institute who received the highest remuneration (including`
  line `allowances and other payments made to such employees) during the financial year and the contributions made by`
  line `such employee during the financial year.`
  line
  line `(3) The statement referred to in sub-section (2) shall indicate whether any such employee is a relative of any`
  line `member of the Board or Academic Council of the Institute and if so, the name of such member; and such other`
  line `particulars as may be determined by the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director shall also be bound to give the complete information and explanations in the report`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) on every reservation, qualification or adverse remark contained in the`
  line `auditors' report.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (40880)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Board to consider statement of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40880&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The statement of accounts, including the balance sheet`
  line `and the statement of income and expenditure, the auditor's report, the report of the Director and other documents`
  line `required to be annexed or attached with such statement, shall be brought before the Board of concerned Institute in`
  line `its meeting not later than three months, from the conclusion of the financial year.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every statement of accounts referred to in sub-section (1) shall be sent to every member of`
  line `the Board not less than twenty-one days before the date of the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The statement of accounts referred to in sub-section (1) shall on its approval by the Board, be`
  line `published on the website of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (40881)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Annual report of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40881&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual report of every Institute shall be prepared under the`
  line `directions of the Board, which shall include, among other matters, steps taken by the Institute towards the`
  line `fulfilment of its objects and an outcome based assessment of the research being undertaken in such`
  line Institute.
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "outcome based assessment of`
  line `research" shall mean an elaboration and analysis of the research conducted and the qualitative and`
  line `quantitative outcomes of such research along with its impact factor and social outcomes.`
  line
  line `(2) The annual report prepared under sub-section (1) shall be submitted to the Board on or before such`
  line `date as may be specified by the Board who shall consider the report in its meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The annual report on its approval by the Board shall be published on the website of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(4) The annual report of each Institute shall be submitted to the Central Government who shall, as soon`
  line `as may be, cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (40882)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Establishment of Coordination Forum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40882&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf, there shall be established a Coordination Forum for`
  line `all the Institutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Coordination Forum shall consist of the following members, namely:---`
  line
  line `^1[(a) an eminent person to be nominated by the Visitor as Chairperson;]`
  line
  line `Provided that the Coordination Forum may select one of its members to act as the chairperson till`
  line `the chairperson is appointed;`
  line
  line `(b) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of the Ministry or Department of the`
  line `Central Government having administrative control of management education, member---ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) two Secretaries in charge of management education of State Governments in which the Institutes`
  line `are located, by rotation, each year, member---ex officio;`
  line
  line `^2[(d) the Chairperson of each Institute--- Member, ex officio];`
  line
  line `(e) the Director of each Institute, member---ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) five persons of eminence, of which at least one shall be a woman, in academia or public service,`
  line `to be selected by a sub-committee constituted by the Coordination Forum.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a member referred to in clause (f) of sub-section (2) shall be three years from`
  line `the date of his nomination.`
  line
  line `(4) The non-official members of the Coordination Forum shall be entitled to such travelling and other`
  line `allowances, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Director of the host Institute where the meeting of the Coordination Forum takes place shall`
  line `be the Member Secretary of the Coordination Forum and shall continue to be the Member-Secretary till a`
  line `new host Institute is selected.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2023, s. 9, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by , s. 9,ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (40883)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Functions of Coordination Forum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40883&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Coordination Forum shall facilitate the sharing of`
  line `experiences, ideas and concerns with a view to enhancing the performance of all Institutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Coordination Forum shall perform the`
  line `following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) recommend to the Central Government, the institution of scholarships including for research`
  line `and for the benefit of students belonging to the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and other`
  line `socially and educationally backward classes of citizens;`
  line
  line `(b) deliberate on such matters of common interest to Institutes as may be referred to it by any`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(c) promote necessary coordination and co-operation in the working of the Institutes;`
  line
  line `(d) review the achievement of policy objectives; and`
  line
  line `(e) perform such other functions as may be referred to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Coordination Forum may constitute such committees as it may consider necessary for carrying`
  line `out its functions under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson of the Coordination Forum shall ordinarily preside at the meetings of the`
  line `Coordination Forum and in his absence, any other member chosen by the members present amongst`
  line `themselves at the meeting, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(5) The Coordination Forum shall submit a report on its functions under sub-section (2) to the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(6) The Coordination Forum shall meet at least once in a calendar year.`
  line
  line `(7) At each meeting of the Coordination Forum, the host institute, which would host the next meeting,`
  line `shall be selected:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Institute shall host the meeting for more than two consecutive years.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (40884)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Acts and proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40884&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `No act of any Institute or the`
  line `Board or the Academic Council or any other body set-up under this Act or the regulations, shall be`
  line `invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy or defect in the constitution thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case; or`
  line
  line `(c) any defect in the selection, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (40885)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Return and information to be provided to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40885&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every Institute shall furnish`
  line `to the Central Government such returns or other information with respect to its policies or activities as the`
  line `Central Government may, for the purpose of reporting to the Parliament or for the making of policy, from`
  line `time to time, require.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (40886)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Institute to be public authority under Right to Information Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40886&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of the Right`
  line `to Information Act, 2005 (22 of 2005) shall apply to each Institute, including Institutes established in publicprivate partnership, as if it were a public authority established by notification issued or order made under`
  line `clause (h) of section 2 of the Right to Information Act, 2005.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification proposed to be issued or order to be made under the Act referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), shall be laid in draft before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of`
  line `thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree`
  line `in disapproving the issue of the notification or order or both Houses agree in making any modification in the`
  line `notification or order, the notification or order shall not be issued or made, as the case may be, shall be issued or`
  line `made only in such modified form as may be agreed upon by both the Houses.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (40887)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40887&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules, for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the conditions and the procedure subject to which the Board may be suspended or dissolved`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(aa) such other powers and duties of the Board under clause (w) of sub-section (2) of section 11;]`
  line
  line `(b) the term and conditions of service of the Director under sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `^2[(ba) the procedure to be adopted for selection of the Director under sub-section (3A) of`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(bb) the manner of termination of services of the Director under sub-section (10) of section 16;]`
  line
  line `(c) the travelling and such other allowances payable to the members of the Coordination Forum for attending its`
  line `meetings or its Committees under sub-section (4) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is to be or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is to be`
  line `made by the Central Government by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2023, s. 10, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by ibid., s. 10, (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (40892)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40892&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, by notification, make regulations not`
  line `inconsistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) tenure, remuneration and terms and conditions of employees of existing Institute under clause`
  line `(d) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) admission of candidates to the various courses of study under clause (b) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of nominating the members from the faculty of respective Institutes under clause (e)`
  line `of sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) the conferment of honorary degrees under clause (g) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) the number of posts, emoluments and the duties and conditions of service of the academic,`
  line `administrative, technical and other staff under clause (j) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) determine performance objectives on the basis of which variable pay may be paid to the`
  line `Director under clause (i) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) to specify by regulations, the fees to be charged for course of study and examinations in the`
  line `Institute under clause (m) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of formation of Departments of teaching under clause (n) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 11;`
  line
  line `(i) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes under clause (o) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(j) the qualifications, classification, terms of office and method of appointment of the academic,`
  line `administrative, technical and other staff of the Institute under clause (p) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 11;`
  line
  line `(k) the constitution of pension, insurance and provident funds for the benefit of the academic,`
  line `administrative, technical and other staff under clause (q) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(I) the establishment and maintenance of buildings under clause (r) of sub-section (2) of section`
  line 11;
  line
  line `(m) the conditions of residence of students of the Institute and levying of fees for residence in the`
  line `halls and hostels and of other charges under clause (s) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of authentication of the orders and decisions of the Board under clause (t) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(o) the meetings of the Board, the Academic Council or any Committee, the quorum at such`
  line `meetings and the procedure to be followed in the conduct of their business under clause (u) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(p) the financial accountability of the Institute under clause (v) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(q) delegate such powers and functions of the Board to the Director under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 11;`
  line
  line `(r) the qualifications, experience and the manner of selection of the independent agency or group`
  line `of experts under sub-section (5) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(s) allowances of the members of the Board for attending meetings under sub-section (6) of section`
  line 12;
  line
  line `(t) such other powers and functions of the Academic Council under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(u) the powers and duties of the Director under sub-section (4) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(v) constitution of such committees and other authorities of the Institute and their duties and`
  line `functions under sub-section (1) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(w) the manner of depositing or investing the moneys credited to the Fund of every Institute under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(x) the manner of application of the Fund of the Institute under sub-section (4) of section 21; and`
  line
  line `(y) any other matter which is to be or may be, specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (40893)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Ordinances how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2019, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "Ordinance" (w.e.f. 8-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40893&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, ^1[Ordinances] shall be`
  line `made by the Academic Council.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder, the Ordinances of`
  line `every Institute may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of students to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees and diplomas of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the degree or diploma courses and to`
  line `the examinations of the Institute, and shall be eligible for degrees and diplomas;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions of award of the fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions and model of appointment and duties of examining bodies, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line
  line `(f) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which is to be or may be provided for by the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(3) All Ordinances made by the Academic Council shall have effect from such date as it may direct,`
  line `but every Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the Board and shall be considered`
  line `by the Board at its next meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall have power by resolution to modify or cancel any such Ordinance and such`
  line `Ordinance shall from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or cancelled, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (40889)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40889&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central Government`
  line `and the first regulation made by the Board under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation shall not be made, the`
  line `rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (40890)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40890&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of the period of three`
  line `years from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (40891)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 40
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711&sectionId=40891&sectionno=39&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00040_201733_1528448470711
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Board of every Institute functioning as such immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act shall continue to so function until a new Board is constituted for that Institute under this Act, but`
  line `on the constitution of a new Board under this Act, the members of the Board holding office before`
  line `such constitution shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(b) every Academic Council or Faculty Council, as the case may be, constituted in relation to every`
  line `Institute before the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to be the Academic Council constituted`
  line `under this Act until an Academic Council is constituted under this Act for that Institute, but on the`
  line `constitution of the new Academic Council under this Act, the members of the Academic Council or Faculty`
  line `Council, as the case may be, holding office before such constitution shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(c) until the first regulations are made under this Act, the rules, and bye-laws of each Institute as in`
  line `force, immediately before the commencement of this Act shall continue to apply to the Institute in so`
  line `far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(d) the Board of National Institute of Industrial Engineering, Mumbai, functioning as such`
  line `immediately before the commencement of the Indian Institutes of Management (Amendment) Act, 2023 shall continue to so function until a new Board is constituted for that Institute under this Act, but`
  line `on such constitution of a new Board under this Act, the Members of the Board holding office before`
  line `such constitution shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(e) the Academic Council constituted in relation to National Institute of Industrial Engineering,`
  line `Mumbai, before the commencement of the Indian Institutes of Management (Amendment) Act, 2023`
  line `shall continue to so function until a new Academic Council is constituted for that Institute under this`
  line `Act, but on the constitution of a new Academic Council under this Act, the Academic Council of the`
  line `National Institute of Industrial Engineering, Mumbai shall cease to function;`
  line
  line `(f) until the first regulations in relation to National Institute of Industrial Engineering, Mumbai are`
  line `made under this Act, the rules and bye-laws of the National Institute of Industrial Engineering,`
  line `Mumbai as in force immediately before the commencement of the Indian Institutes of Management`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2023 shall continue to apply to the National Institute of Industrial Engineering,`
  line `Mumbai with necessary modifications and adaptations insofar as they are not inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act.]`
  line
  line `^2[(g) until the first Board of the Indian Institute of Management, Guwahati is constituted under this`
  line `Act, all the powers and functions which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be exercised or`
  line `performed by or on behalf of such Board on the commencement of the Indian Institutes of`
  line `Management (Amendment) Act, 2025, shall be exercised and performed by such person or persons as`
  line `the Central Government may direct in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, without prejudice to the provisions of this Act, if it considers so`
  line `necessary and expedient, by notification, take such measures, which may be necessary for the smooth`
  line `transfer of the existing Institute to the corresponding Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2023, s. 11 (w.e.f. 16-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 2025, s. 3 (w.e.f. 01-09-2025).`
